pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `key` ( `version` char(32) CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_general_ci NOT NULL DEFAULT 'unknown', `edition` char(32) CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_general_ci NOT NULL DEFAULT 'unknown', `type` char(32) CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_general_ci NOT NULL DEFAULT 'unknown', `key` char(30) CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_general_ci NOT NULL, `verified` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0', `verifiedOn` datetime DEFAULT NULL, `invalidated` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0', `invalidatedOn` datetime DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`version`,`edition`,`type`,`key`), KEY `version` (`version`), KEY `edition` (`edition`), KEY `type` (`type`), CONSTRAINT `key_edition` FOREIGN KEY (`edition`) REFERENCES `edition` (`name`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE, CONSTRAINT `key_type` FOREIGN KEY (`type`) REFERENCES `type` (`name`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE, CONSTRAINT `key_version` FOREIGN KEY (`version`) REFERENCES `version` (`name`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE ) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
